    <div class="container conference" id="lead-section-conference">
        <div class="row conference">
            <h2>LDI Conference</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="row conference">
            <img class="img-responsive img-conference" src="img/ldi_2015.jpg">
        </div>
        <div class="row conference">
            <p>The Leadership Development Institute (LDI) is our first conference of the year that offers a great opportunity for new and returning members to learn more about what it’s like to be in FBLA. It is a great way to get introduced to FBLA and to meet new people with similar interests in business. Also, it is one of the only conferences that are not associated with competition. Attending LDI will guide you to business concepts and FBLA competitive events with amazing workshops led by business professionals.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container conference">
        <div class="row conference">
            <h2>Bay Section Leadership Conference (Regionals)</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="row conference">
            <img class="img-responsive img-conference" src="img/section_2015.jpg">
        </div>
        <div class="row conference">
            <p>The Bay Section Conference, also known as Regionals, is the first competition for FBLA members. This is where competitors gather for one day to take written tests on their events and to watch candidate’s campaign for section officers. Regionals usually takes place in a local high school in our bay area in January or February.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
    <div class="container conference">
        <div class="row conference">
            <h2>State Leadership Conference</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="row conference">
            <img class="img-responsive img-conference" src="img/state_2015.jpg">
        </div>
        <div class="row conference">
            <p>The State Leadership Conference (SLC) is the second competition for FBLA members. Members who qualified from the Bay Section (regional) Conference get the chance to compete with same events at the state level. If you didn’t qualify and still want to attend SLC, Don’t worry! Even if you did not qualify for an event in bay section, you can still compete with new events that start in SLC. The State Leadership Conference is 3 days long, and takes place in Northern or Southern California, alternating every year. This conference offers members the chance not only to compete, but also to have fun and meet other FBLA members from all across California.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
        <div class="container conference">
        <div class="row conference">
            <h2>National Leadership Conference</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="row conference">
            <img class="img-responsive img-conference" src="img/national_2016.jpg">
        </div>
        <div class="row conference">
            <p>The National Leadership Conference (NLC) is the final round of competition for FBLA members. You can meet FBLA members from all across the nation while competing. Note that this conference is generally only available for the members who qualified from SLC.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

